race.comment: DON'TCHA THINK (9) lumped 60kgs when easily accounted for over 1400m at Eagle Farm last start. Strips fitter after two runs back and has been in the money at three of four third-up runs. Makes plenty of appeal dropping a massive 6kgs for this assignment. RUN LUCY RUN (5) led all the way and gave nothing else a chance when second-up last time out over this course and distance. Should at least hold that performance level at this early stage of the prep. Can cross and lead again - sure to prove tough to catch. TREPORTI (1) hasn't won for around 14 months but did run a cheeky race over 1400m at Eagle Farm recently in a Class 4. Worth some thought in this slightly easier race. Lightly raced four-year-old NORTH COURT (4) has been freshened up since filling a minor placing over 1666m here six weeks ago. Has two wins and a close fourth from three runs at this trip. Right in contention. SMART ACTION (7) can improve after a modest return at the Gold Coast last start.
